# ⌨️ Essential Keyboard Shortcuts for Windows 10/11 and Linux

A handy reference guide for common keyboard shortcuts that improve productivity and navigation across Windows and Linux systems.

---

## 🪟 Windows 10 & 11 Shortcuts

| Shortcut                  | Action                                     |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `Win + D`                | Show desktop                               |
| `Win + E`                | Open File Explorer                         |
| `Win + L`                | Lock your PC                               |
| `Win + Tab`              | Open Task View                             |
| `Alt + Tab`              | Switch between open apps                   |
| `Ctrl + Shift + Esc`     | Open Task Manager                          |
| `Win + S`                | Open Search                                |
| `Win + I`                | Open Settings                              |
| `Win + X`                | Open Quick Link menu                       |
| `Ctrl + C / V / X`       | Copy / Paste / Cut                         |
| `Ctrl + Z / Y`           | Undo / Redo                                |
| `Win + Arrow Keys`       | Snap windows left, right, maximize, etc.   |
| `Win + Shift + S`        | Screenshot selection (Snipping Tool)       |
| `Alt + F4`               | Close current window                       |

---

## 🐧 Linux Desktop Shortcuts (Ubuntu/GNOME-based)

| Shortcut                  | Action                                     |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `Ctrl + Alt + T`         | Open Terminal                              |
| `Super + A`              | Show all applications                      |
| `Super + D`              | Show desktop                               |
| `Alt + Tab`              | Switch between windows                     |
| `Ctrl + Alt + L`         | Lock screen                                |
| `PrtSc`                  | Screenshot full screen                     |
| `Shift + PrtSc`          | Screenshot selection                       |
| `Ctrl + Alt + Del`       | Show logout/shutdown menu                  |
| `Super + Left/Right`     | Tile window left/right                     |
| `Alt + F4`               | Close window                               |
| `Ctrl + Shift + N`       | Create new folder in File Manager          |
| `Alt + F2`               | Run command                                |

> **Note**: `Super` refers to the **Windows key** on most keyboards.

---

## 📝 Tips

- Use **`Ctrl + L`** in browsers and file managers to jump to the address bar.
- Use **`Ctrl + Shift + T`** to reopen closed tabs in most browsers.
- Keyboard shortcuts may differ slightly based on Linux desktop environment (GNOME, KDE, XFCE, etc.).

